# 🧾 Simplest GST Billing App  
A lightweight and efficient **GST billing application** designed to streamline **invoice generation, inventory management, and bookkeeping**. Ideal for businesses looking for a hassle-free billing solution with accuracy and ease.  

## 🚀 Features  
### 🏢 Business & Billing  
📌 **Generate GST Invoices** – Create professional invoices with tax calculations.  
📦 **Inventory Management** – Keep track of stock levels and products.  
📊 **Bookkeeping** – Maintain transaction records and balances.  
📂 **Customer Management** – Store and retrieve customer details.  

### 🔒 Security & Efficiency  
🔐 **User Authentication** – Secure login system.  
📄 **Export Reports** – Download invoices and reports in multiple formats.  
🚀 **Fast & Lightweight** – Built with Django for speed and reliability.  

## 🏗️ Tech Stack  
| Tech        | Usage                          |  
|------------|--------------------------------|  
| **Django**  | Backend Framework              |  
| **SQLite**  | Database Management            |  
| **Bootstrap** | Frontend UI Framework         |  
| **Virtualenv** | Environment Management       |  

## 📂 Folder Structure  
```
simplest-gst-billing/
│── billing/            # Core Billing Module  
│── inventory/          # Inventory Management  
│── users/              # Authentication & Users  
│── templates/          # HTML Templates  
│── static/             # CSS & JS Files  
│── db.sqlite3          # Database  
│── manage.py           # Django Management Script  
│── requirements.txt    # Dependencies  
│── README.md           # Documentation  
```

## 🎯 Installation & Setup  

### 🔹 1. Clone the Repository  
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/simplest-gst-billing.git
cd simplest-gst-billing
```  

### 🔹 2. Create Virtual Environment & Install Dependencies  
```bash
virtualenv -p python3 venv  
source venv/bin/activate  
pip install -r requirements.txt  
```  

### 🔹 3. Apply Migrations & Run Server  
```bash
python manage.py migrate  
python manage.py runserver  
```  

🎉 **Now, open `http://127.0.0.1:8000/` and start managing your invoices!**  

